# Contracts

Governed by parent **Event Platform PRD §14.4 and §26**. Windows repo consumes; does not define API shape.

## HTTP API (platform)

| Method | Path | Auth | Body |
|---|---|---|---|
| GET | `/api/print-queue/pending` | `Bearer relay_…` | — |
| POST | `/api/print-queue/{id}/complete` | `Bearer relay_…` | — |
| POST | `/api/print-queue/{id}/failed` | `Bearer relay_…` | `{ "message"?: string }` |

Base URL from setup code `api_url` field (no trailing slash).

## Pending response

Validate against `schemas/pending-job.response.json`. Windows **prints `badge_html` only**. `badge_document` is validated for forward compatibility — never rendered client-side.

## Setup code wire format

```
DESK-<base64url(JSON)>
```

Decode → validate against `schemas/desk-setup-code.v1.json` → extract `secret`, `api_url`, `desk_name`.

## Changing contracts

1. Parent PRD §26 amendment in **platform repo** first.
2. Platform ships schema + deploy.
3. Copy schemas to this repo; bump `schemas/platform-pin.json`.
4. Coordinated Windows release if required fields change.

See `INTEGRATION.md` release coordination table.

## Pinning

Never track platform `main` without a commit SHA in `platform-pin.json`. Contract tests must pass before merge.
